<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>救生艇新闻：博客——保护人类</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/</link><description></description><lastBuildDate>Tue, 03 Mar 2026 12:33:20 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>纳米技术如何使一种旧的白血病药物的功效增强 22,000 倍</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/how-nanotech-made-an-old-leukemia-drug-22000x-stronger</link><description>结构纳米医学——帮助我们研制出新冠疫苗的东西——现在可能是有效治疗血癌的关键，并且已经取得了显着的早期效果。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/how-nanotech-made-an-old-leukemia-drug-22000x-stronger.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 03 Mar 2026 12:33:17 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/how-nanotech-made-an-old-leukemia-drug-22000x-stronger</guid></item><item><title>额颞叶痴呆迷你大师班：将诊断最佳实践融入实践</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/frontotemporal-dementia-mini-masterclass-integrating-best-practices-on-diagnosis-into-practice</link><description>不当行为何时会指向更深层次的问题？ &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/frontotemporal-dementia-mini-masterclass-integrating-best-practices-on-diagnosis-into-practice.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 03 Mar 2026 12:18:17 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/frontotemporal-dementia-mini-masterclass-integrating-best-practices-on-diagnosis-into-practice</guid></item><item><title>循环酮体和事件心血管结果和死亡率：来自英国生物银行的见解</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/circulating-ketone-bodies-and-incident-cardiovascular-outcomes-and-mortality-insights-from-the-uk-biobank</link><description>在大量人群中，较高的酮体水平与心血管事件和死亡率增加相关。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/circulating-ketone-bodies-and-incident-cardiovascular-outcomes-and-mortality-insights-from-the-uk-biobank2.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 03 Mar 2026 12:03:17 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/circulating-ketone-bodies-and-incident-cardiovascular-outcomes-and-mortality-insights-from-the-uk-biobank</guid></item><item><title>将高通量功能测定应用于体内神经科学的挑战和机遇</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/challenges-and-opportunities-in-adapting-high-throughput-functional-assays-for-in-vivo-neuroscience</link><description>CRISPR 筛选和大规模并行报告基因检测等高通量功能检测已经改变了培养细胞中基因调控的研究，但它们向神经科学的转化仍然有限。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/challenges-and-opportunities-in-adapting-high-throughput-functional-assays-for-in-vivo-neuroscience2.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 03 Mar 2026 11:48:17 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/challenges-and-opportunities-in-adapting-high-throughput-functional-assays-for-in-vivo-neuroscience</guid></item><item><title>使用荧光探针和工程酶进行精确肿瘤成像</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/precision-tumor-imaging-with-a-fluorescence-probe-and-engineered-enzymes</link><description>成功的癌症手术取决于外科医生切除肿瘤的能力，同时尽量减少对健康组织的伤害。外科医生目前使用发光染料来标记癌细胞，以帮助与健康细胞区分开来，但这些染料并不完美，也会照亮一些健康组织。包括东京大学在内的研究人员首次开发出一种生物正交荧光探针和一种匹配的报告酶，该酶可以在目标肿瘤位点选择性地激活探针。这使得在背景非常低的情况下实现高对比度肿瘤可视化。这项研究是在小鼠身上进行的。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/precision-tumor-imaging-with-a-fluorescence-probe-and-engineered-enzymes.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 03 Mar 2026 11:33:17 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/precision-tumor-imaging-with-a-fluorescence-probe-and-engineered-enzymes</guid></item><item><title>微生物从空间站上的陨石中获取金属</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/microbes-harvest-metals-from-meteorites-aboard-space-station</link><description>如果人类要探索深空，就不能落下一位小乘客：微生物。事实上，我们不可能将它们抛在身后，因为它们生活在我们的身体、表面和食物中。了解它们对太空条件的反应至关重要，但它们也可能成为我们探索太空的宝贵伙伴。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/microbes-harvest-metals-from-meteorites-aboard-space-station.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 03 Mar 2026 11:18:17 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/microbes-harvest-metals-from-meteorites-aboard-space-station</guid></item><item><title>珍珠和牡蛎：冷球蛋白血症中枢神经系统参与导致的可逆性白质脑病和帕金森病</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/pearls-oy-sters-reversible-leukoencephalopathy-and-parkinsonism-due-to-cns-involvement-in-cryoglobulinemia</link><description>什么是代谢功能障碍相关的脂肪肝病？ &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/pearls-oy-sters-reversible-leukoencephalopathy-and-parkinsonism-due-to-cns-involvement-in-cryoglobulinemia2.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 03 Mar 2026 11:03:17 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/pearls-oy-sters-reversible-leukoencephalopathy-and-parkinsonism-due-to-cns-involvement-in-cryoglobulinemia</guid></item><item><title>被忽视的静电力如何驱动未来的电机</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/how-an-overlooked-electrostatic-force-could-drive-the-motor-of-the-future</link><description>当我们听到用电移动物体时，大多数人都会想到“拉力”。正电荷和负电荷相互吸引，将物体吸引在一起。人们很自然地认为这种吸引力（称为静电力）是使物体移动的原因。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/how-an-overlooked-electrostatic-force-could-drive-the-motor-of-the-future.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 03 Mar 2026 10:48:17 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/how-an-overlooked-electrostatic-force-could-drive-the-motor-of-the-future</guid></item><item><title>中子照亮手性声子的磁舞</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/neutrons-illuminate-the-magnetic-dance-of-chiral-phonons</link><description>中子散射为磁性晶体中旋转的集体原子振动提供了新的、更广阔的视角。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/neutrons-illuminate-the-magnetic-dance-of-chiral-phonons2.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 03 Mar 2026 10:33:17 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/neutrons-illuminate-the-magnetic-dance-of-chiral-phonons</guid></item><item><title>NASA 的 MAVEN 首次发现火星上存在类闪电活动的证据</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/nasas-maven-detects-first-evidence-of-lightning-like-activity-on-mars</link><description>在筛选美国宇航局火星大气和挥发性演化（MAVEN）航天器在过去十年中收集的大量数据时，科学家们发现了一种熟悉的电磁信号类型，通常由闪电引起。这一罕见的发现代表了火星上闪电活动的首次直接迹象。团队最近&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/nasas-maven-detects-first-evidence-of-lightning-like-activity-on-mars.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 03 Mar 2026 10:18:17 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/nasas-maven-detects-first-evidence-of-lightning-like-activity-on-mars</guid></item></channel></rss>